{{see|zero}}

==Translingual==
===Cardinal number===
*[[w:Arabic numerals|Arabic numerals]]: 0
*[[w:Chinese numerals|Chinese numerals]]: 零, 〇
===Pronunciation===
''see'' [[zero]]
===Noun===
'''0''' (''plural:'' '''[[0s]]''')
# The [[cardinal number]] [[zero]] indicating absence of any quantity. 
#:''The only scored '''0'''.''
# [[numeral]] corresponding to the number zero.
#:''The score keeper put up the final'' 0 ''at the end of the last inning.''
# A [[digit]] in [[decimal]] and every other [[base]] numbering system, including [[binary]], [[octal]], and [[hexadecimal]].
#:''Hexadecimal numbers ending in'' 0 ''are divisible by 16.''
#The origin, starting point, or fixed reference point, especially for a measurement.
#:''The '''0''' for the Celcius scale is 273 degrees Kelvin.''
# Nothing, nought. 
#:''The shipment was lost, so they had'' 0 ''in stock.''
#{{mathematics}} the [[identity element]] with respect to [[addition]] in a [[ring]].
#: <math>a</math>+0=<math>a</math>
#(''computer science'') [[bit]] state corresponding to binary digit 0, or [[off]] or [[FALSE]].
#{{mathematics}} A [[Boolean]] or truth value corresponding to FALSE.
#:''The Boolean domain contains only'' 0 ''and 1.''
====Synonyms====
*number: [[cipher]], [[nil]], [[nought]], [[null]]
*digit: [[slashed zero]]
====Derived terms====
*[[0th]], [[ordinal number]] form
*[[10]], [[20]], [[100]], etc.; cardinal number representations containing [[digit]] '''0'''

===Adjective===
'''0'''
# Of no or zero quantity; of [[cardinality]] zero.
#:''In the desert'' 0 ''cm precipitation per month is common.''
#Of the origin, starting point, especially for a measurement.
#:''The ice will begin to melt at'' 0 ''degrees C.''

